@bolkedebruin Good catch - I admit that I didn't see it either at first. 

The title in the commit is `limit scope to user email only AIRFLOW-386`, which does not adhere to guidelines, where as the title in the PR follows the correct guidelines : `[AIRFLOW-386] limit scope to user email only for github oauth`

@jlowin I thought the pr tool did some checks on the title, but maybe it's checking the PR title not the commit title? 

<img width="985" alt="screenshot 2016-08-01 20 04 16" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/581734/17315759/376b3240-5823-11e6-9183-d2fba04afcdc.png">

@spektom Looks pretty good. A few suggestions: 
- You've added the new config element in 2 of the 3 customary places in configuration.py. You excluded it from TEST_CONFIG, probably because it it not important to test. However, please add it for completeness. 
- Follow the items mentioned in https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/AIRFLOW/Contributors%27+Guide, such as sticking to a 50 char subject line (you have 73) and squashing your commits into a single one.
